						<div id="siteSub" class="noprint">From Wikiquote</div>
					</div>
					<div id="contentSub"><div id="mw-content-subtitle"><span class="mw-redirectedfrom">(Redirected from <a href="/w/index.php?title=Compete&amp;redirect=no" class="mw-redirect" title="Compete">Compete</a>)</span></div></div>
					
					
					<div id="mw-content-text" class="mw-body-content"><div class="mw-content-ltr mw-parser-output" lang="en" dir="ltr"><figure class="mw-default-size" typeof="mw:File/Thumb"><a href="/wiki/File:Jacque_Fresco_and_lemon_tree.jpg" class="mw-file-description"><img src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b2/Jacque_Fresco_and_lemon_tree.jpg/250px-Jacque_Fresco_and_lemon_tree.jpg" decoding="async" width="250" height="167" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b2/Jacque_Fresco_and_lemon_tree.jpg/500px-Jacque_Fresco_and_lemon_tree.jpg 1.5x" data-file-width="3504" data-file-height="2336" /></a><figcaption>Competition is dangerous, socially offensive... What kind of competition is there in your body? Suppose your brain said, "I'm the most important organ!" And the liver said, "I am. And I want a Free Enterprise system!" You'd rot away in a month if every organ of your body went out for itself.  ~ <a href="/wiki/Jacque_Fresco" title="Jacque Fresco">Jacque Fresco</a>  <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=RVOPkGAtt48">1974 Larry King Interview</a> </figcaption></figure> 
<figure class="mw-default-size" typeof="mw:File/Thumb"><a href="/wiki/File:William_Butler_Yeats_by_John_Singer_Sargent_1908.jpg" class="mw-file-description"><img src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/70/William_Butler_Yeats_by_John_Singer_Sargent_1908.jpg/250px-William_Butler_Yeats_by_John_Singer_Sargent_1908.jpg" decoding="async" width="250" height="331" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/70/William_Butler_Yeats_by_John_Singer_Sargent_1908.jpg/500px-William_Butler_Yeats_by_John_Singer_Sargent_1908.jpg 1.5x" data-file-width="604" data-file-height="800" /></a><figcaption>For how can you compete,<br />Being honor bred, with one<br />Who, were it proved he lies,<br />Were neither shamed in his own<br />Nor in his neighbors’ eyes?<br />~ <a href="/wiki/W._B._Yeats" class="mw-redirect" title="W. B. Yeats">W. B. Yeats</a></figcaption></figure>
<figure class="mw-default-size" typeof="mw:File/Thumb"><a href="/wiki/File:Manufacturing_productivity_and_wages_in_the_United_States.svg" class="mw-file-description"><img src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/44/Manufacturing_productivity_and_wages_in_the_United_States.svg/250px-Manufacturing_productivity_and_wages_in_the_United_States.svg.png" decoding="async" width="250" height="187" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/44/Manufacturing_productivity_and_wages_in_the_United_States.svg/500px-Manufacturing_productivity_and_wages_in_the_United_States.svg.png 1.5x" data-file-width="750" data-file-height="560" /></a><figcaption>I was perpetuating my own oppression by engaging in competitive capitalist practices that ensure the smooth functioning of the system as the exploiting minority profits in more ways than one off the division and disunity engendered by competition, so prevalent amongst the exploited. Look around: competition, euphemistically called “individuality,” permeates and is systematically promoted to the masses of people while the corporate conglomerations and Fortune 500 are busy “merging and monopolizing.” ~ <a href="/wiki/Kevin_Rashid_Johnson" title="Kevin Rashid Johnson">Kevin Rashid Johnson</a></figcaption></figure>
<figure class="mw-default-size" typeof="mw:File/Thumb"><a href="/wiki/File:Eugene_V._Debs,_1907.jpg" class="mw-file-description"><img src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/9f/Eugene_V._Debs%2C_1907.jpg/250px-Eugene_V._Debs%2C_1907.jpg" decoding="async" width="250" height="280" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/9f/Eugene_V._Debs%2C_1907.jpg/500px-Eugene_V._Debs%2C_1907.jpg 1.5x" data-file-width="1620" data-file-height="1816" /></a><figcaption>I would be ashamed to admit that I had risen from the ranks. When I rise it will be with the ranks, and not from the ranks. ~ <a href="/wiki/Eugene_Debs" class="mw-redirect" title="Eugene Debs">Eugene Debs</a></figcaption></figure>
<figure class="mw-default-size" typeof="mw:File/Thumb"><a href="/wiki/File:Friedrich_Engels_colored_portrait.png" class="mw-file-description"><img src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/26/Friedrich_Engels_colored_portrait.png/250px-Friedrich_Engels_colored_portrait.png" decoding="async" width="250" height="366" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/26/Friedrich_Engels_colored_portrait.png/500px-Friedrich_Engels_colored_portrait.png 1.5x" data-file-width="819" data-file-height="1200" /></a><figcaption>Abolish competition and replace it with association. ~ <a href="/wiki/Friedrich_Engels" title="Friedrich Engels">Friedrich Engels</a></figcaption></figure>
<figure class="mw-default-size" typeof="mw:File/Thumb"><a href="/wiki/File:Bastiat.jpg" class="mw-file-description"><img src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e6/Bastiat.jpg/250px-Bastiat.jpg" decoding="async" width="250" height="313" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e6/Bastiat.jpg/500px-Bastiat.jpg 1.5x" data-file-width="786" data-file-height="983" /></a><figcaption>Competition is merely the absence of oppression. ~ <a href="/wiki/Fr%C3%A9d%C3%A9ric_Bastiat" title="Frédéric Bastiat">Frédéric Bastiat</a></figcaption></figure>
<figure class="mw-default-size" typeof="mw:File/Thumb"><a href="/wiki/File:Eduardo_Galeano_(Feria_del_Libro_de_Madrid,_31_de_mayo_de_2008).jpg" class="mw-file-description"><img src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/3c/Eduardo_Galeano_%28Feria_del_Libro_de_Madrid%2C_31_de_mayo_de_2008%29.jpg/250px-Eduardo_Galeano_%28Feria_del_Libro_de_Madrid%2C_31_de_mayo_de_2008%29.jpg" decoding="async" width="250" height="338" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/3c/Eduardo_Galeano_%28Feria_del_Libro_de_Madrid%2C_31_de_mayo_de_2008%29.jpg/500px-Eduardo_Galeano_%28Feria_del_Libro_de_Madrid%2C_31_de_mayo_de_2008%29.jpg 1.5x" data-file-width="2520" data-file-height="3409" /></a><figcaption>The dominant culture of the world teaches us that The Other is a threat, that our fellow human beings are a danger. We will all continue to be exiles in one form or another as long as we continue to accept the paradigm that the world is a racetrack or a battlefield. ~ <a href="/wiki/Eduardo_Galeano" title="Eduardo Galeano">Eduardo Galeano</a></figcaption></figure>
<figure class="mw-default-size" typeof="mw:File/Thumb"><a href="/wiki/File:Nick_Hanauer_Laura_Flanders_2016.png" class="mw-file-description"><img src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/9a/Nick_Hanauer_Laura_Flanders_2016.png/250px-Nick_Hanauer_Laura_Flanders_2016.png" decoding="async" width="250" height="283" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/9a/Nick_Hanauer_Laura_Flanders_2016.png/500px-Nick_Hanauer_Laura_Flanders_2016.png 1.5x" data-file-width="1255" data-file-height="1419" /></a><figcaption>It isn't capital that creates economic growth, it's people... it isn't self-interest that promotes the public good, it's reciprocity; and  it isn't <a class="mw-selflink selflink">competition</a> that produces our prosperity, it's cooperation.  ~<a href="/wiki/Nick_Hanauer" title="Nick Hanauer">Nick Hanauer</a></figcaption></figure>
<figure class="mw-default-size" typeof="mw:File/Thumb"><a href="/wiki/File:Justice_Oliver_Wendell_Holmes_standing.jpg" class="mw-file-description"><img src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/ad/Justice_Oliver_Wendell_Holmes_standing.jpg/250px-Justice_Oliver_Wendell_Holmes_standing.jpg" decoding="async" width="250" height="337" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/ad/Justice_Oliver_Wendell_Holmes_standing.jpg/500px-Justice_Oliver_Wendell_Holmes_standing.jpg 1.5x" data-file-width="3931" data-file-height="5295" /></a><figcaption>Free competition is worth more to society than it costs. ~ <a href="/wiki/Oliver_Wendell_Holmes,_Jr." class="mw-redirect" title="Oliver Wendell Holmes, Jr.">Oliver Wendell Holmes, Jr.</a></figcaption></figure>
<figure class="mw-default-size" typeof="mw:File/Thumb"><a href="/wiki/File:Joseph_Schumpeter_ekonomialaria.jpg" class="mw-file-description"><img src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/5f/Joseph_Schumpeter_ekonomialaria.jpg/250px-Joseph_Schumpeter_ekonomialaria.jpg" decoding="async" width="250" height="333" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/5f/Joseph_Schumpeter_ekonomialaria.jpg/500px-Joseph_Schumpeter_ekonomialaria.jpg 1.5x" data-file-width="1572" data-file-height="2096" /></a><figcaption>In economic life competition is never completely lacking, but hardly ever is it perfect. ~ <a href="/wiki/Joseph_Schumpeter" title="Joseph Schumpeter">Joseph Schumpeter</a></figcaption></figure>
<p><b><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Competition" class="extiw" title="w:Competition">Competition</a></b> is the rivalry of two or more parties over something. Competition occurs naturally between living organisms which coexist in the same environment. For example, <a href="/wiki/Animals" title="Animals">animals</a> compete over <a href="/wiki/Water" title="Water">water</a> supplies, <a href="/wiki/Food" title="Food">food</a>, and mates. In addition, <a href="/wiki/Humans" class="mw-redirect" title="Humans">humans</a> compete for <a href="/wiki/Attention" title="Attention">attention</a>, <a href="/wiki/Wealth" title="Wealth">wealth</a>, <a href="/wiki/Prestige" title="Prestige">prestige</a>, and <a href="/wiki/Fame" title="Fame">fame</a>, or as a form of <a href="/wiki/Recreation" title="Recreation">recreation</a>.  Competition is often considered to be the opposite of cooperation, however wherever the world is dominated by corporations &amp; extreme wealth, mixtures of cooperation, competition, &amp; corruption are the norm.
</p>
